HEADWORD: Surculate
<hw>Sur"cu*late</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>surculatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>surculare</ets> to purne, from
<ets>surculus</ets> a shoot, sprout. See <er>Surcle</er>.]</ety> <def>To
purne; to trim.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
